DefaultReaderConfiguration.preQueryCheck: select count(*) from REPOS_NAME where REPOS_NAME.ServerTimestamp >= ?
DefaultReaderConfiguration.queryString: select REPOS_NAME.EventID, REPOS_NAME.SourceIP, REPOS_NAME.ClientTimestamp, REPOS_NAME.ClientMS, REPOS_NAME.ServerTimestamp, REPOS_NAME.SessionID, REPOS_NAME.Component, REPOS_NAME.Severity, REPOS_NAME.Grouping, REPOS_NAME.Originator, REPOS_NAME.OriginatorType, REPOS_NAME.Target, REPOS_NAME.TargetType, REPOS_NAME.SubTarget, REPOS_NAME.Text1, REPOS_NAME.Text2, REPOS_NAME.Text3, REPOS_NAME.Value1, REPOS_NAME.Value2, REPOS_NAME.Value3, REPOS_NAME.MIMEType, REPOS_NAME.DataSize, REPOS_NAME.Data, REPOS_NAME.Signature from REPOS_NAME where REPOS_NAME.ServerTimestamp >= ? order by REPOS_NAME.ServerTimestamp limit ?

string.toolTipText:
Amount of rows to attempt to pull in one query, recommended 10000. This value should be
larger than the expected peak value of events that will be received in one second,
but not so large as to cause the reader to run out of memory.
